   <Table name="FieldSystem">
      <Title>
      Contains information about the systems of field centres used in the SSA.
      </Title>
      <Description>
      The Schmidt photographic surveys were based around predefined systems of
      field centres. This table lists the ones employed in the photographic
      surveys used to generate the SSA.
      </Description>

      <Column datatype="int" name="systemID">
         <Description>The system of survey fields used for the survey                          </Description>
         <UCD>ID_MAIN </UCD>
         <UcdPlus> </UcdPlus>
      </Column>

      <Column datatype="char" name="name">
         <Description>The name of the system, eg. "ESO/SRC", "POSS-I" etc.</Description>
         <UCD>NOTE</UCD>
         <UcdPlus> </UcdPlus>
      </Column>

      <Column datatype="real" name="centrePitch">
         <Description>The pitch of the field centres
         </Description>
         <UCD>OBS_DIFF</UCD>
         <UcdPlus> </UcdPlus>
         <Units>deg</Units>
      </Column>
   </Table>

   <Table name="Survey">
      <Title>
      Contains information about the Schmidt photographic surveys in the SSA.
      </Title>
      <Description>
      The SuperCOSMOS Science Archive was created from machine scans of
      the UK, ESO and Palomar Oschin Schmidt telescope surveys undertaken
      from 1949 to 2003. Each individual passband survey (eg. SERC-J/EJ,
      POSS-I E etc.) is described in this table.
      </Description>

