   <Table name="IsoCalVersion">
      <Title>
       Information concerning all isophotal photometric calibrations in the SSA.
      </Title>
      <Description>
                                                                                               
       Over the course of several implementations of the SuperCOSMOS Sky Survey,
       several revised calibrations of the isophotal photometry have been done.
       This table stores the calibration version numbers, start and end dates
       relevant for those calibrations, and a short description for each version
       of the isophotal photometry scale (note that this is not applicable to
       point-like sources brighter than around 3 magnitudes above the respective
       plate limits; in any case, the profile magnitude scale should be used for
       point sources).
      </Description>
